<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="319" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="14.[754,1341,2528,2953]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis box="[755,910,2528,2561]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
Galeriscus jackson: Thomas, 1894, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3699972301" box="[840,1231,2571,2600]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">
Mianzini, Masailand, 
<collectingCountry box="[1140,1227,2571,2600]" name="Kenya" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[754,1341,2528,2953]" pageId="14" pageNumber="319">Some authors consider B. jackson: conspecific with the Black-footed Mongoose (B. migripes), but others believe that there are sufficient skin and skull differences to consider them as two separate species. Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="319" type="distribution">
